Camera
over here.

01:22.383 --> 01:23.451
Hello?
(beeps)

01:29.490 --> 01:31.092
Was there ever a
moment you-you thought

01:31.225 --> 01:32.660
about stopping
with Metallica,

01:32.827 --> 01:34.428
or the whole band
was falling apart?

01:34.562 --> 01:37.331
Was it a kind of a power
struggle between you and him?

01:37.498 --> 01:39.333
REPORTER 3: How did you
manage to solve this crisis?

01:39.500 --> 01:40.768
Where in God's name
are you getting

01:40.901 --> 01:42.103
all this aggression
from on this new album?

01:42.236 --> 01:43.304
Where's it
coming from?

01:43.471 --> 01:45.106
Why did it take so long
to release an album

01:45.239 --> 01:46.273
with the
new songs?

01:46.407 --> 01:48.776
REPORTER 4: After 20
years, is it possible

01:48.909 --> 01:50.344
to retain the fire that,
you know,

01:50.511 --> 01:51.879
you guys once had
at the beginning?

01:52.046 --> 01:53.314
Do you think
the young generation

01:53.481 --> 01:54.715
of met-metal
fans will...

01:54.882 --> 01:56.050
accept the
new album?

01:56.217 --> 01:58.986
85 million records,
<i>22</i> years...

01:59.153 --> 02:02.189
I think it's 11 albums in
various official releases.

02:02.356 --> 02:04.325
One word...
(Hetfield laughs)

02:05.759 --> 02:07.461
Oh, my God.

02:07.595 --> 02:10.163
One word to span our career?

02:10.330 --> 02:11.465
Uh...

