But... I mean, I don't see
what it does to this.

29:36.142 --> 29:37.777
ULRICH: I think that's
how you hear it, dude.

29:37.910 --> 29:39.378
I mean, that's fine.

29:39.545 --> 29:41.046
I'm just trying to do
something different.

29:41.213 --> 29:42.948
I mean, I'm...

29:43.082 --> 29:46.018
I'm used to having
the drummer do the...

29:46.185 --> 29:47.453
beat part.

29:47.586 --> 29:48.454
(laughing):
You know what I mean?

29:48.587 --> 29:49.622
Holding it together.

29:49.755 --> 29:51.056
ULRICH:
Urn...

29:51.223 --> 29:54.460
what I'm hearing is...

29:56.729 --> 29:58.697
Gotta choose my words
carefully here.

30:01.033 --> 30:03.002
Urn...

30:03.169 --> 30:04.470
it's pretty straightforward.

30:04.603 --> 30:07.006
And the guitar
shit, it's...

30:07.173 --> 30:08.741
you know, it's
a little stock.

30:08.908 --> 30:10.176
So I started trying to

30:10.342 --> 30:12.678
introduce some kind of
edge to it, from the drums.

30:12.845 --> 30:14.847
HETFIELD: Those things
we throw out to each other

30:15.014 --> 30:16.182
are complete bullshit.

30:16.348 --> 30:17.817
You know?

30:17.950 --> 30:19.018
"It sounds too stock.

30:19.185 --> 30:20.352
It sounds too normal to me."

30:20.519 --> 30:22.488
That... I mean...

30:23.856 --> 30:25.257
Do you know what I mean?

30:25.424 --> 30:27.059
You're saying this shit... so...

30:27.226 --> 30:28.661
you can get your point across

30:28.794 --> 30:30.196
about doing a drum beat.

30:30.362 --> 30:31.897
I mean...

30:32.064 --> 30:33.532
you know,
it doesn't hold any water.

30:33.699 --> 30:34.867
ULRICH:
To you.

30:35.034 --> 30:35.868
HETFIELD:
It doesn't!

30:36.035 --> 30:37.269
I think it's fucking stock!

30:37.436 --> 30:39.538
What... which part of that
is unclear to you?

30:39.705 --> 30:42.074
I think it sounds stock
to my ears.

30:42.241 --> 30:44.210
I mean, do you want me
to write it down?

30:45.578 --> 30:46.779
I think... HETFIELD: Oh,
yeah, please write it down.

30:46.946 --> 30:48.180
...It feels stock, okay?
HETFIELD: I can't hear you.

30:48.314 --> 30:49.949
So I... HETFIELD:
No, when you say...

30:50.115 --> 30:51.617
you're telling me what
to play, right now.

30:51.784 --> 30:54.220
You're telling me, "You should
play with what's Kirk's doing,"

30:54.386 --> 30:55.588
and I'm telling you it's stock.

30:55.754 --> 30:57.756
Dude... fine.

30:57.923 --> 30:59.091
You know what, you guys?

30:59.258 --> 31:00.392
Why don't we
just go in there

31:00.559 --> 31:01.627
and just hammer
it out, all right,

31:01.794 --> 31:03.963
instead of hammering
on each other?

31:04.129 --> 31:05.931
I mean, we're in shit moods
and we're not going to get

31:06.098 --> 31:08.234
anything done in there today. ULRICH: All
we want to do is pick a fuckin' fight.

31:08.400 --> 31:10.436
And you...
I don't want to pick a fight.

31:10.603 --> 31:11.971
This is... it's so silly.

31:12.137 --> 31:13.138
You're just sitting there going,

31:13.305 --> 31:14.907
"I'm in a really
pissy mood, and..."

31:15.074 --> 31:16.575
HETFIELD:
And I fuckin' told you

31:16.742 --> 31:18.077
straight up that I was.

31:18.244 --> 31:19.912
Right. And what are
you trying to do?

31:20.079 --> 31:21.580
I'm not trying to
do fuckin' shit!

31:21.747 --> 31:22.581
You're just sitting here

31:22.748 --> 31:24.717
being a complete dick.

31:26.252 --> 31:28.254
You're-you're really
helping matters.

31:28.420 --> 31:29.955
You're really good at that.

31:30.122 --> 31:31.490
I was straight up with you,

31:31.657 --> 31:33.459
and I told you
I'm in a shit mood!

31:33.626 --> 31:34.927
And what have you been doing?

31:35.094 --> 31:36.996
Fuckin' picking at me all night.

31:37.162 --> 31:38.464
Come on, guys.

31:38.631 --> 31:40.099
We've got better things to do.

31:40.266 --> 31:41.300
Right?
