39:46.852 --> 39:48.220
<i>and, I mean, looking back on...</i>

39:48.353 --> 39:50.088
<i>I mean, what is that--
18, 19 years ago--</i>

39:50.255 --> 39:52.891
<i>I mean, I just felt so
alienated because it was just</i>

39:53.024 --> 39:56.762
<i>so far removed from the
upbringing that I'd come from.</i>

39:56.928 --> 39:59.464
Well, here's to you, my friends.

39:59.631 --> 40:00.932
<i>ULRICH:
But then, at the same time,</i>

40:01.099 --> 40:03.735
<i>I'm starting to realizing now
that the sort of</i>

40:03.869 --> 40:05.570
<i>depressive things that show up</i>

40:05.704 --> 40:07.906
<i>as a result of the alcohol
and stuff like that.</i>

40:08.039 --> 40:09.608
<i>It was just very difficult</i>

40:09.775 --> 40:12.144
<i>for him to communicate
from the heart.</i>

40:12.310 --> 40:15.580
<i>You want some or not'? Not hide behind
a lot of these different fronts.</i>

40:15.714 --> 40:17.949
<i>Whether it's alcohol,
that gives him</i>

40:18.116 --> 40:20.519
<i>a false sense of strength or...</i>

40:20.685 --> 40:22.421
<i>the front man in Metallica or,</i>

40:22.554 --> 40:25.957
<i>you know, macho bullshit
and all that stuff.</i>

40:26.124 --> 40:28.427
All right, now you guys
are drunk and I'm drunk.

40:28.560 --> 40:31.129
Now this is the fun part, man.

40:31.296 --> 40:32.297
I want to help him.

40:32.464 --> 40:33.698
I want to be there for him.

40:33.865 --> 40:35.634
And I want to do the best I can

40:35.801 --> 40:39.004
to make him the best person
that he can be.

40:39.171 --> 40:41.773
So I-I don't know how the fuck
it's gonna play out.

40:41.907 --> 40:43.875
<i>II'</i>

41:05.163 --> 41:07.499
<i>HAMMETT: It's really healthy
for me to be here.</i>

41:07.666 --> 41:09.868
<i>Without any pressure</i>

41:10.035 --> 41:12.237
or anything related
to the band <i>or...</i>

41:12.404 --> 41:16.675
anyone who would remind me
of-of the band.

41:16.842 --> 41:20.645
<i>And, uh, recognize what's real.</i>

41:22.514 --> 41:24.683
<i>Our sessions with Phil</i>

41:24.850 --> 41:27.819
<i>really stirred up a lot
of things in James that</i>

41:27.953 --> 41:31.556
<i>he felt that
he needed to address.</i>

41:31.723 --> 41:35.193
Mentally, it's really taken...
taken its toll on myself.

41:35.360 --> 41:37.863
You know, it's...
I'm-I'm very worried about him.

41:38.029 --> 41:39.931
And, you know,

41:40.098 --> 41:43.235
whenever you
check yourself into rehab,

41:43.401 --> 41:44.836
they don't...

41:44.970 --> 41:46.271
they don't focus on,
you know,

41:46.438 --> 41:47.839
the fact that
you're an alcoholic.

41:47.973 --> 41:49.274
They go much deeper, you know?

41:49.441 --> 41:50.942
I mean, they go way deep.

41:51.109 --> 41:52.878
They crack you open
